The paper discusses recent approaches to commonsense question answering, which is a task that falls under the intersection of natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related tasks. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of knowledge resources and integration methods, which are common topics in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). The paper also evaluates models on multiple benchmarks, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories.
